to remove the local change: git resest -- hard [old stable commit id] or git reset -- hard HEAD~1 [to delete last commit]
and to remove remote changes: git revert HEAD
to list all tags : git tag
to delete an old tage locally: git tag -d "tagename", OR git tag â€”delete "tagename"
to delete an old tag remotly: git push --delete origin tagname
rebase command: this command like git merge and used with feature branch workflow to keep the development history clean. example:
i am working on new feature and there is a new update commits in master branch, if i merge the master with my new feature branch the log will not have my commit history.
so will use the rebse command to switch my base commit to the last updated commit in the branch and then if i merged here my history will not lost


